                        <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-check"></i> Use <a href="#sdks">HTML, Bootstrap, or Material Design</a> to easily create applications.</li>
                        <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-check"></i> <a href="#components">Angular boilerplate</a> for Bootstrap and Material Design frameworks.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <h5>&nbsp;</h5>
                <div class="col-md-3"><img src="~/Images/ico/comb.svg"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <div class="content" id="section2">
        <section class="section section-1">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-sm-4">
                        <img alt="Sass and Less support" src="Images/sass-less.png" class="img-responsive">
                        <h3 style="font-size: 22px;"><strong>Preprocessors</strong></h3>
                        <p>Currently in ISD we're using Bootstrap and Material which both ship with vanilla CSS, but its source code utilizes the two most popular CSS preprocessors, <a href="javascript:void(0);">Less</a> and <a href="javascript:void(0);">Sass</a>. Quickly get started with templates that come with precompiled CSS.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-sm-4">
                        <img alt="Responsive across devices" src="Images/devices.png" class="img-responsive">
